law.text:
The Department shall proportionately distribute the annual appropriation of Program funds as follows:
if a county is a qualifying local government, and no municipal corporation in the county is a qualifying local government, the Department shall distribute Program funds to the county based on the county's share of the State population;
if a county is a qualifying local government, and a municipal corporation in the county is also a qualifying local government, the Department shall:
determine the county's proportionate share of Program funds based on the county's share of the State population; and
from the amount of Program funds determined under item (i) of this item, distribute:
to each qualifying local government in the county that is a municipal corporation, an amount of Program funds based on the municipal corporation's share of the county population; and
to the county, the balance of the county's share of Program funds; or
if a county is not a qualifying local government, but a municipal corporation in the county is a qualifying local government, the Department shall:
determine the county's proportionate share of Program funds based on the county's share of the State population; and
distribute to each qualifying local government in the county that is a municipal corporation, a proportionate share of the amount of Program funds determined under item (i) of this item based on the municipal corporation's share of the county's population.
